			<h3>Hotspot Data Structure</h3>
			<p>Each hotspot should have the following structure:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>id</strong>: Unique identifier for the hotspot</li>
				<li><strong>x</strong>: Horizontal position as percentage (0-100)</li>
				<li><strong>y</strong>: Vertical position as percentage (0-100)</li>
				<li><strong>title</strong>: Main heading for the hotspot</li>
				<li><strong>description</strong>: Detailed content (supports HTML)</li>
				<li><strong>icon</strong>: Optional emoji or icon class</li>
				<li><strong>link</strong>: Optional direct link URL</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Use Cases</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Product feature explanations</li>
				<li>Interactive maps and floor plans</li>
				<li>Architectural drawings with annotations</li>
				<li>Equipment diagrams and manuals</li>
				<li>Educational infographics</li>
				<li>Tour guides and location markers</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Positioning</h3>
			<p>Hotspots are positioned using percentage coordinates:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>x: 0</strong> = Left edge, <strong>x: 100</strong> = Right edge</li>
				<li><strong>y: 0</strong> = Top edge, <strong>y: 100</strong> = Bottom edge</li>
				<li><strong>x: 50, y: 50</strong> = Center of the image</li>
			</ul>
